throughput. Use Min Changeover when the shop is changeover-bound."},{key:"spt",label:"Shortest Processing Time",shortLabel:"SPT",objective:"Minimise the sum of every job's completion time — close the queue fastest in aggregate. Short jobs land in front of long ones; the solver re-orders globally rather than placing one at a time.",whenToUse:"High order count and throughput dominates the KPI sheet. Especially powerful with a mix of short and long jobs — the heuristic SPT would let long jobs starve.",watchOut:"Long jobs can still slip late. Pair with a due-date floor or use EDD when on-time delivery matters as much as throughput."},{key:"min_changeover",label:"Minimum Changeover",shortLabel:"Min CO",objective:"Minimise total setup minutes across the schedule by picking task sequences per machine that group same-SKU runs. A true optimiser, not a sort.",whenToUse:"Changeovers are your largest hidden cost — paint, food, pharma. The SKU changeover rules table needs to be populated for the solver to find groupings.",watchOut:'Sparse SKU changeover rules → the objective is mostly zero and any schedule "wins". Also: due-date drift is possible, so always check the Late count.'},{key:"max_utilization",label:"Maximum Utilization",shortLabel:"Max Util",objective:"Minimise makespan — the moment the LAST job finishes. Equivalent to packing machines tight so the gantt finishes as soon as possible.",whenToUse:"Machine-hour is your cost driver (leased equipment, single shift, batch production). You want every machine busy and the overall horizon compressed.",watchOut:"Individual jobs may slip past their due date if compressing the makespan demands it. Use EDD if per-order on-time delivery beats throughput."}],Yr=Object.fromEntries(Ob.map(t=>[t.key,t])),xL={cp_edd:"edd",cp_spt:"spt",cp_min_changeover:"min_changeover",cp_max_utilization:"max_utilization",cp_multi_edd:"edd",cp_multi_spt:"spt",cp_multi_min_changeover:"min_changeover",cp_multi_max_utilization:"max_utilization",multi_edd:"