 when to use it",className:t||"inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full border border-indigo-300 bg-indigo-100 px-2.5 py-1 text-[11px] font-semibold text-indigo-800 shadow-sm hover:bg-indigo-200 hover:border-indigo-400",children:[e.jsx("svg",{className:"h-3.5 w-3.5",fill:"none",stroke:"currentColor",viewBox:"0 0 24 24",children:e.jsx("path",{strokeLinecap:"round",strokeLinejoin:"round",strokeWidth:2,d:"M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M12 2a10 10 0 100 20 10 10 0 000-20z"})}),n]}),e.jsx(a1,{open:s,onClose:()=>a(!1),title:"Scheduling strategies",subtitle:"Each strategy sorts jobs differently. Pick one — or stack several for a composite rank.",footer:e.jsxs(e.Fragment,{children:["Tip: picking more than one strategy creates a"," ",e.jsx("span",{className:"font-semibold text-amber-700",children:"Composite"})," — jobs are ranked by each strategy and the average rank wins."]}),children:e.jsx("div",{className:"divide-y divide-gray-100",children:Ob.map(r=>e.jsxs("div",{className:"px-5 py-4",children:[e.jsxs("div",{className:"flex items-baseline gap-2",children:[e.jsx("h4",{className:"text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900",children:r.label}),e.jsx("span",{className:"text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-indigo-600",children:r.shortLabel})]}),e.jsx("p",{className:"mt-1.5 text-sm text-gray-700",children:r.objective}),e.jsxs("div",{className:"mt-2 grid gap-2 sm:grid-cols-2",children:[e.jsxs("div",{className:"rounded-md border border-emerald-100 bg-emerald-50/60 px-3 py-2",children:[e.jsx("div",{className:"text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-emerald-700",children:"When to use"}),e.jsx("div",{className:"mt-0.5 text-xs text-emerald-900",children:r.whenToUse})]}),e.jsxs("div",{className:"rounded-md border border-amber-100 bg-amber-50/60 px-3 py-2",children:[e.jsx("div",{className:"text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-700",children:"Watch out"}),e.jsx("div",{className:"mt-0.5 text-xs text-amber-900",children:r.watchOut})]})]})]},r.key))})})]})}const hL=[{key:"min_changeover",label:"Minimum Changeover",shortLabel:"Min CO",objective:"Group orders with shared attributes (colour, viscosity, allergen) onto the same plant so each facility runs compatible families and avoids costly setups.",whenToUse:"Changeovers are the biggest hidden cost — paint, food, pharma. Keeping red-to-red or allergen-compatible runs together recovers the most capacity.",watchOut:"May send an urgent order to a farther plant just to preserve a colour family. Always glance at the late-jobs count before applying."},{key:"balance_load",label:"Balance Load",shortLabel:"Load",objective:"Spread orders across plants so no single facility is overloaded and none is idle. Aims for even utilization.",whenToUse:"Demand is lumpy across regions and one plant keeps drowning while another sits idle. Use this to flatten the peaks and improve reliability.",watchOut:"A perfectly balanced plan may increase changeovers because families get split across plants. Compare the changeover-delta column before applying."},{key:"due_date_first",label:"Due Date First",shortLabel:"EDD",objective:"Place urgent orders on the plant that can finish them soonest — even if that plant is already loaded. Prioritises on-time delivery over efficiency.",whenToUse:"A customer-promise crunch, end-of-quarter deliveries, or a handful of hot orders that cannot slip. Trust on-time % over utilization %.",watchOut:"Can push a plant past 100% utilization. Pair with Balance Load if that plant also has long-horizon backlog you don’t want to starve."},{key:"material_ready",label:"Material Ready",shortLabel:"RM",objective:"Allocate to the plant that can actually start soonest — based on on-hand raw materials plus incoming receipts. Honest about supply.",whenToUse:"Multi-plant network where RM is held at specific sites (regional warehouses, consignment stock). Avoids sending orders to plants that look free on paper but have no feedstock.",watchOut:"Can cluster demand on the RM-rich plant and starve others. Compare Max Load column against Balance Load before applying — and top up inventory at under-utilized plants if the split is unhealthy."}];function pL({className:t="",label:n="What do strategies mean?"}){const[s,a]=u.useState(!1);return e.jsxs(e.Fragment,{children:[e.jsxs("button",{type:"button",onClick:()=>a(!0),title:"Learn what each allocation strategy does and when to use it",className:t||"inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full border border-indigo-300 bg-indigo-100 px-2.5 py-1 text-[11px] font-semibold text-indigo-800 shadow-sm hover:bg-indigo-200 hover:border-indigo-400",children:[e.jsx("svg",{className:"h-3.5 w-3.5",fill:"none",stroke:"currentColor",viewBox:"0 0 24 24",children:e.jsx("path",{strokeLinecap:"round",strokeLinejoin:"round",strokeWidth:2,d:"M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M12 2a10 10 0 100 20 10 10 0 000-20z"})}),n]}),e.jsx(a1,{open:s,onClose:()=>a(!1),title:"Allocation strategies",subtitle:"Each strategy decides WHICH plant runs each order. Pick one to preview the moves — nothing is applied until you confirm.",footer:e.jsxs(e.Fragment,{children:["After you pick a strategy, review the"," ",e.jsx("span",{className:"font-semibold text-brand-primary",children:"moves"})," panel (top-right of the plants grid) before clicking ",e.jsx("span",{className:"font-semibold",children:"Apply"}),"."]}),children:e.jsx("div",{className:"divide-y divide-gray-100",children:hL.map(r=>e.jsxs("div",{className:"px-5 py-4",children:[e.jsxs("div",{className:"flex items-baseline gap-2",children:[e.jsx("h4",{className:"text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900",children:r.label}),e.jsx("span",{className:"text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-indigo-600",children:r.shortLabel})]}),e.jsx("p",{className:"mt-1.5 text-sm text-gray-700",children:r.objective}),e.jsxs("div",{className:"mt-2 grid gap-2 sm:grid-cols-2",children:[e.jsxs("div",{className:"rounded-md border border-emerald-100 bg-emerald-50/60 px-3 py-2",children:[e.jsx("div",{clas