dule:"The Plan loop scheduler.",capacity:"Capacity heatmap by line and day.",lines:"Production line / section definitions.",suppliers:"Supplier master + procurement simulation.",order_splitting:"Split section-step orders proportionally across all eligible machines so a single job runs in parallel across multiple heads. Per-section opt-out available on the Lines page.",leaflet_workflow:"Adds leaflet-specific SKU fields (type, dimensions, GSM, paper, UPS, folds) and a per-machine max_folds eligibility rule on Folding-line machines.",strict_serial_jobs:"Block the next job from starting on any machine until the current job has finished on every machine in its routing. Use for shops that require one-job-at-a-time execution; turn off for the default pipeline overlap.",visual_setup:"Enables the /graph page: a node-based canvas for setting up the plant (machines, lines, transit) in one visual map instead of the individual Settings pages. Read-only in v1; editing rolls out in follow-up phases.",configs:"Define tenant-specific SKU attributes (e.g., GSM, Color). Used as inputs for per-machine constraints and config-driven changeovers. PR1 enables only the attribute schema CRUD; SKU/machine/scheduling wiring follows in later PRs.",warehouses:"Warehouse nodes on the graph + CRUD. Required for any supply-chain modelling beyond the plant floor.",regions:"Region (demand) nodes + Region picker on the Intake page. When on, orders can be keyed by destination region so the resolver picks the cheapest plant.",supply_chain_lanes:"SHIPS_TO and SERVES lane edges on the graph canvas, plant-header node, and dashed plant→line edges. Visualises the chain from plant to region. Requires Warehouses + Regions.",warehouse_stock:"Stock-on-hand panel inside the CTP card + per-warehouse stock CRUD. Enables ATP (Available-to-Promise) short-circuit when stock can cover an order. Requires Warehouses.",capable_to_promise:"Capable-to-Promise preview on the order intake page: earliest delivery date, chosen lane, breakdown, alternatives. Requires Regions + Supply-Chain Lanes.",logistics_gantt:"Synthetic ship + last-mile rows appended below production rows on the Plan Gantt, with a Logistics toggle on the filter bar.",manual_labor:'Machines opt into a person requirement (toggle on the Machines page). Their SKU per-machine throughput is then read as "units per person per hour"; an Available People page in the plan flow assigns a person count per machine, which the scheduler multiplies into the effective processing rate. Setup/changeover/charging are unaffected.',poultry_allocation:'Poultry production planning module: per-SKU BOM editor, yield calculator, cutting plans, bin-board inventory, allocate-orders flow with ATP, and an audit log. Surfaces a "Poultry" dropdown in the top nav with six sub-pages. Enable only for poultry tenants.',shrimp_daily_plan:`Shrimp daily-planning module: a "/plan/daily" page that pulls the raw material received (external DB/ERP, manual fallback), lets the planner set people per section (= MachineCategory — the capacity lever), and recommends which orders to run over a rolling 30-day due-date horizon with per-section capacity utilisation, then finalises into the scheduler. A section's effective rate = people × rate/person/hour. Enable only for shrimp tenants.`,material_planning:'Controls whether the SCHEDULER enforces raw-material availability. Material is a planning concern, not a sequencing one — so this is OFF by default and orders schedule on machine feasibility alone (no "insufficient materials" blocking). Daily-plan tenants gate material in the daily plan, so the scheduler always skips it for them regardless of this toggle. Turn this ON only for a non-daily-plan tenant that wants the scheduler itself to refuse orders lacking raw material.',inventory_policies:'Make-to-stock replenishment. Adds an Inventory Policies settings page where the planner sets target_stock / safety_stock / reorder_point per (SKU, scope) where scope is a warehouse, plant, or region. A manual "Run replenishment scan" button reads STOCKED_AT stock for each policy and auto-creates a JobOrder when effective stock drops at or below the reorder point. Emitted jobs land at stage `order` for planner review by default; flip per-policy `auto_approve` to push them straight to `awaiting`. Designed for MTS shops that produce against forecasted demand rather than pure customer orders.',ansa_rfq:`Ansapack RFQ suite: folding-carton + leaflet cost calculators (56 box styles, interlock nesting, board/ink/finishing/route costing), an LLM enquiry-to-quote workflow, estimates with revisions, masters (paper/board, product codes, leaflet items, clients, rate card), and PDF quote/job-card generation. Surfaces an "RFQ" tab in the top nav. On finalize it creates a JobOrder for an existing SKU, or mints a new SKU with an auto-mapped production route (AFC steps matched to the tenant's Lines) and then the JobOrder. Replaces the legacy RFQ Automation / Leaflet Workflow surface. Enable only for the Ansapack tenant.`,schedule_sharing:'Public view-only schedule links. Planners get a Share button on the Schedule page that mints a per-plant link; people WITHOUT a login open it to view the Gantt and add comments (visible to the planner too). Enforced in the backend, not just the UI: turning this OFF immediately disables every existing link for this tenant (visitors see "link not valid"); turning it back on revives the same links. Off by default — this exposes schedule data to anyone holding the URL, so enable deliberately.'};function wL(){const[t,n]=u.useState([]),[s,a]=u.useState(!0),[r,i]=u.useState(null),[l,o]=u.useState(null),[d,c]=u.useState(null),[m,h]=u.useState({}),[x,p]=u.useState(null),[g,y]=u.useState(!1),[j,f]=u.useState(null),[b,v]=u.useState([]),[_,k]=u.useState(null),[w,N]=u.useState(null),[E,R]=u.useState(""),F=async L=>{f(L.user_id);try{L.enabled?await m1(L.user_id):await u1(L.user_id),n(z=>z.map(J=>({...J,users:J.users.map(Y=>Y.user_id===L.use